New Tang Dynasty Television's (NTD) 5th International Figure Painting Competition was held at the Salmagundi Club in New York from November 24 through November 30, 2019.

This year's figure painting competition received more than 400 submissions from 258 artists in 46 countries. The judging panel then selected 103 of these works for exhibition at the Salmagundi Club in New York, and 63 of these works were honored at an awards ceremony held on Thursday, November 26, 2019.

snippet.textDisplay:
After fight one, I saw these videos of Andy Ruiz out with his young dumb friends after the fight enjoying the new good life of Andy's millions, it gave me a sense of eeriness. Something didn't look right here. He was doing too many interviews like flying to Mexico City showing off his belts to a foreign president. In Mexico I didn't see giant crowds around him because they knew he's going back to America and live the good life and it's not in Mexico.
Seeing Andy eat as much as he wants, drinking whatever he wanted, partying, pissing his money away with four over expensive cars a house before its time, jewelry, expensive watch, something was amiss here. Doing too many interviews which were boring because he doesn't read much obviously nor read the news which makes for a one-dimensional person boring only talking about his Mexican blood that won the fight instead of training properly.
I'm not seeing him doing serious running road work or training out in the gym most of the time, instead of going home to his lovely wife and family, he's partying again with his young dumb friends and none of them are encouraging him to train. Andy Ruiz should be ashamed of himself, he let us all down when we were expecting a good fight all we saw was him dragging his heels, no longer swinging fast punches, no longer being aggressive, he was totally out of shape and at almost 300 pounds. What a big waste of a great fighter. His performance was so bad he'll never get a rematch he has to prove himself fighting others again what a waste of time and extra effort have he trained right for fight 2 to begin with. He may never get a rematch in a heavyweight title fight. He'll probably lose his next fight because of poor training and then his life has been wasted. If he spends too much of his earnings he may be broke by the time he's 40 years old, a wasted life. He reminds me of the stupid things I've done in life.
